 \___)(____/(____) Release Information
****************************************
Computational Science Environment

Build Date: 20231122
Release: 2023Q3

NOTE: To access CSE modules, first module load cseinit or module load cseinit-noloads
      module load cseinit --> loads environment of the CSE build and provides access to CSE modules 
      module load cseinit-noloads --> makes no changes to existing module environment and provides access to CSE modules
      CSE modules will work correctly after loading cseinit, as prerequisites modules are loaded and conflicts unloaded
      CSE module cseinit-noloads allows the user to choose among compatible prerequisites.
      For Intel build of CSE, module setup is the same except use module cseinit-intel instead.

OpenMPI 3.1.6 is default for Workstations and some HPCs
CSE Intel and Cray builds utilize a system's MPI whenever possible
OpenMPI 2.1.6 is available for standalone use, and not compatible with CSE's cse/python module

CSE modules cse/python3 and cse/miniforge/latest are identical with conda available
CSE module  cse/python (python2) and other python2 modules cannot be utilized with cse/miniforge (python3)
Python 3.12.8 provided by cse/miniforge/latest

Contact Information
